{"id":"343624236_Black-Box_Use_of_One-Way_Functions_is_Useless_for_Optimal_Fair_Coin-Tossing","abstract":"A two-party fair coin-tossing protocol guarantees output delivery to the honest party even when the other party aborts during the protocol execution. Cleve (STOC–1986) demonstrated that a computationally bounded fail-stop adversary could alter the output distribution of the honest party by (roughly) 1/r (in the statistical distance) in an r-message coin-tossing protocol. An optimal fair coin-tossing protocol ensures that no adversary can alter the output distribution beyond 1/r.","authors":["Hemanta Maji","Mingyuan Wang"],"meta":["August 2020","DOI:10.1007/978-3-030-56880-1_21","In book: Advances in Cryptology – CRYPTO 2020 (pp.593-617)"],"references":["320850059_When_Does_Functional_Encryption_Imply_Obfuscation","277292952_Martingales_collective_coin_flipping_and_discrete_control_processes_Extended_Abstract","269702475_Black-Box_Separations_for_One-More_Static_CDH_and_Its_Generalization","266247920_Can_Optimally-Fair_Coin_Tossing_Be_Based_on_One-Way_Functions","262936805_Adaptive_Security_of_Constrained_PRFs","262166873_On_the_Instantiability_of_Hash-and-Sign_RSA_Signatures","225198696_On_the_Black-Box_Complexity_of_Optimally-Fair_Coin_Tossing","225144239_1p-Secure_Multiparty_Computation_without_Honest_Majority_and_the_Best_of_Both_Worlds","225128191_Perfect_Zero-Knowledge_Arguments_for_NPUsing_Any_One-Way_Permutation","224967896_Limits_of_Random_Oracles_in_Secure_Computation","341076848_Signatures_from_Sequential-OR_Proofs","340985082_On_Black-Box_Extensions_of_Non-interactive_Zero-Knowledge_Arguments_and_Signatures_Directly_from_Simulation_Soundness","339254868_One-More_Assumptions_Do_Not_Help_Fiat-Shamir-type_Signature_Schemes_in_NPROM","337460785_Estimating_Gaps_in_Martingales_and_Applications_to_Coin-Tossing_Constructions_and_Hardness","336393230_How_to_play_any_mental_game_or_a_completeness_theorem_for_protocols_with_honest_majority","335861307_On_the_Sec